public class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello");
    }
}

// Compilation: javac compiles to .class bytecode (COMPILED)
// Execution: JVM interprets bytecode (INTERPRETED)
// Same program: both compiled and interpreted simultaneously
```

